comment.body:
@baentsch Many thanks for your feedback! I will address the points you mentioned.

CCI shows above that all tests passed, but if you look closely all BUT OpenSSH was tested. I registered a new job *ubuntu_x64_openssh* because I did not want to mess with your other tests you mention to be "some kind of SSL-using", which SSH is not. Why CCI did not automatically run the other job I don't know, on my side (CCI) it just did it. But I guess for simplicitiy's sake it is easier to add OpenSSH to the other tests and omit the fact that it is not SSL based. So it would be retested upon a change of OpenSSL with the others, which would not be the end  of the world.

Long story short: Should I integrate the test job into your existing job or keep the new one I created?
